{"type":"message","id":"b46d4ccc","parentId":"2a7e79b7","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:00:43.253Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Same result, Unity exits with code 1 due to license issue. The key issue is the \"No valid Unity Editor license found\" error.\n\nLooking at the license error more carefully:\n```\n[Licensing::Module] Error: Access token is unavailable; failed to update\n[Licensing::Client] Error: Code 500 while processing request (status: Unable to update licenses. Errors: Cannot load ULF license: The digital signature is invalid.,Token not found in cache)\n```\n\nThe license might need to be activated first through the Unity Hub, or we need to run with the correct user context that has the license.\n\nLet me try running the bat file from the Unity project directory, but with a different approach - maybe through a scheduled task or with proper elevation. Since I can't use elevated mode, let me check if there's an interactive session where Unity has been manually activated.\n\nActually, wait - the key here is that this requires the license to be activated. When running from Unity Hub or from the Unity Editor normally, the license is cached for the current user. But in batch mode, it needs to be able to access the license.\n\nLet me check the Unity Hub license status.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_zGPkdoZEPiVjCqDFtgh40533","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check Unity Hub license status\n$hubPath = \"$env:LOCALAPPDATA\\Unity\\Hub\"\nWrite-Host \"Unity Hub path: $hubPath\"\nif (Test-Path $hubPath) {\n    Get-ChildItem $hubPath -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName | Select-Object -First 10\n}\n\n# Check for Unity license files\n$licPath = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\AppData\\Roaming\\Unity\"\nWrite-Host \"`nUnity license path: $licPath\"\nif (Test-Path $licPath) {\n    Get-ChildItem $licPath -Recurse -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object FullName | Select-Object -First 20\n}\n\n# Check if there are any running Unity processes currently\n$unity = Get-Process Unity -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nWrite-Host \"`nRunning Unity processes:\"\n$unity | Select-Object Id, ProcessName, StartTime","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":124,"output":511,"cacheRead":16640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17275,"cost":{"input":0.00001736,"output":0.00014308000000000002,"cacheRead":0.00046592,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0006263600000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778670037456,"responseId":"9f4b9c14-5db4-41e5-b893-c4388d04c31d"}}
