{"type":"message","id":"cfa63115","parentId":"d07b44c8","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:02:07.141Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Even running as SYSTEM with highest privileges, the license validation still fails! The problem is the license itself - \"Cannot load ULF license: The digital signature is invalid.\" The license file at C:\\ProgramData\\Unity\\Unity_lic.ulf has an invalid digital signature.\n\nThis means the license needs to be reactivated through Unity Hub. But since this is a background task, I can't do interactive activation.\n\nLet me try another approach - maybe I should check if there's a way to run the Unity Editor in a way that doesn't require batch mode license validation. Actually, wait - let me check if the Unity Hub has a CLI that can activate the license.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the issue is that Unity 2020.3 uses a new \"entitlement-based licensing\" system that replaces the old ULF serial-based system. The ULF license file for serial F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2 is considered \"invalid\" by the new system.\n\nThe user would need to:\n1. Open Unity Hub\n2. Sign in with their Unity account\n3. Activate the license through the new licensing system\n\nOr alternatively, the user could configure the BuildPipeline to work without the CDN upload step, so they could run the Unity Editor interactively instead.\n\nLet me check what the status is and provide a clear report to the main agent.\n\nActually, let me try one more thing - check if there's a Unity Hub CLI to activate the license.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_iejBgx7xu2xblrTK3rYc9492","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if Unity Hub CLI exists\n$hubCli = \"$env:LOCALAPPDATA\\Unity\\Hub\\unity-hub.exe\"\nif (Test-Path $hubCli) {\n    Write-Host \"Unity Hub found: $hubCli\"\n    & $hubCli --help 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 20\n} else {\n    Write-Host \"Unity Hub CLI not found at: $hubCli\"\n    # Try alternate locations\n    $altPaths = @(\n        \"$env:LOCALAPPDATA\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\Unity Hub.exe\",\n        \"$env:PROGRAMFILES\\Unity Hub\\Unity Hub.exe\",\n        \"$env:PROGRAMFILES(x86)\\Unity Hub\\Unity Hub.exe\"\n    )\n    foreach ($p in $altPaths) {\n        if (Test-Path $p) {\n            Write-Host \"Found: $p\"\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# Also check if there's a Unity License tool\n$licTool = \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity\\Hub\\Editor\\2020.3.49f1\\Editor\\Data\\Resources\\Licensing\\Client\\Unity.Licensing.Client.exe\"\nif (Test-Path $licTool) {\n    Write-Host \"`nLicensing client found\"\n    & $licTool --help 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 10\n}","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":596,"output":662,"cacheRead":24960,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26218,"cost":{"input":0.00008344,"output":0.00018536,"cacheRead":0.00069888,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0009676800000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778670121171,"responseId":"e681eef2-e7c8-4a24-9774-3dcba9526fba"}}
