{"type":"message","id":"03317837","parentId":"1acc9855","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:02:11.744Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The Unity Hub is installed at `C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\Unity Hub.exe`. Let me try to use the Licensing Client to activate the license via the Hub. But this is likely interactive - it needs the user to sign in.\n\nLet me try a different approach. Maybe I can try to launch the Unity Editor in a non-batch mode first, to get the license activated. Or maybe I should try running the batch mode from within an interactive Unity Editor session that's already running.\n\nActually, let me look at this from a different angle. The notes in TOOLS.md say \"运行需要管理员权限（Unity 许可证校验）\". So the previous updates used this approach and worked. Maybe the license expired or needs to be refreshed.\n\nLet me check if there's another Unity license that might work, or if we need to go through the Unity Hub to reactivate.\n\nActually, I think the real solution here is that the main agent needs to ask the user to open Unity Hub and reactivate the license. This isn't something I can fix programmatically. Let me provide a clear report about what happened.\n\nWait, let me try one more thing - maybe I can use the Unity Hub command line to activate the license.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_Zz2QKL6BYgtDGw0oio7q2957","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check Unity Hub CLI switches\n& \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\Unity Hub.exe\" --help 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 30\nWrite-Host \"---\"\n& \"C:\\Program Files\\Unity Hub\\Unity Hub.exe\" help 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 30","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":367,"output":377,"cacheRead":26112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26856,"cost":{"input":0.000051380000000000006,"output":0.00010556000000000001,"cacheRead":0.000731136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.000888076}},"st