{"type":"message","id":"5b55d889","parentId":"ebb730b4","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:02:47.369Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The license syncing requires a network connection to the licensing server. This might be because the company's network uses a licensing server that's different from the default public one.\n\nActually, looking at this again, the key issue is that the serial license `F4-H1R5-BQNV-8DQZ-Q4V2-XXXX` is a PRO (Plus/Pro) license with an invalid digital signature. The new licensing system doesn't recognize the old ULF format correctly.\n\nI think the best approach here is to:\n1. Report the license issue clearly\n2. Suggest the user reactivate the license through Unity Hub\n\nBut wait - the user (主人) would know about this, since other developers have likely run the same pipeline. Let me check if there's a different way the hot update is done in practice. Maybe there's another script or configuration.\n\nActually, let me just report this issue. I've exhausted the automated options:\n1. Unity batch mode fails due to \"No valid Unity Editor license found\"\n2. The existing license file at C:\\ProgramData\\Unity\\Unity_lic.ulf has an invalid digital signature\n3. Even when running as SYSTEM, the license can't be validated\n4. The licensing client can't sync entitlements (likely needs to be configured or needs the user to log in through Hub)\n\nLet me clean up the temporary files and provide a clear report.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_grJNSy9WkMbI0UfteEMB1583","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Cleanup: remove temporary task and scripts\nschtasks /Delete /TN \"UnityHotUpdate_Temp\" /F >nul 2>&1\nRemove-Item \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\tools\\hotupdate-scripts\\RunUnityElevated.bat\" -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nRemove-Item \"E:\\Solo\\nightoffullmoon\\tools\\hotupdate-scripts\\CreateTask.bat\" -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue\nWrite-Host \"Cleanup do